oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of DuPont High School students
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Composite photograph of the DuPont High School Class of 1936. DuPont produced gunpowder under contract with the U.S. Army and built the largest smokeless powder plant in the world during WWI. Production ceased with the end of the war and the government sold the property. DuPont returned to the area in 1928. At the time these seniors graduated, DuPont was producing Rayon and Cellophane.
